            <h2 class="text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6 text-cyan-300">Beginner's Animation Guide & Principles</h2>
            <div class="liquid-glass p-8 rounded-xl space-y-8">

                <!-- 1. The Fundamentals -->
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white mb-4 border-b border-cyan-700 pb-2">Your First Animated Loop (5 Steps)</h3>
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-4 text-lg">
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Conceptualize:</strong> Start with a short, simple idea (e.g., a ball bouncing).</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Sketch Keyframes:</strong> Draw the most important frames (start, peak, end).</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">In-Betweens:</strong> Fill in the frames between your keyframes to create smooth motion.</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Timing & Spacing:</strong> Adjust the speed of movement. Closer frames = slower; farther frames = faster.</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Review & Repeat:</strong> Watch your loop and refine the motion until it feels right.</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>

                <!-- 2. The 12 Principles -->
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white mb-4 border-b border-cyan-700 pb-2">The 12 Principles of Animation</h3>

                    <!-- Image of the 12 Principles -->
                    <img src="https://i0.wp.com/scifi.radio/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/principlesOfAnimation-1.jpg?fit=736%2C552&ssl=1"
                         alt="Chart illustrating the 12 Principles of Animation"
                         class="w-full max-w-2xl mx-auto rounded-lg shadow-2xl mb-6 border-2 border-cyan-500/50"
                         onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='https://placehold.co/736x552/0f172a/38bdf8?text=12+Principles+Image';"
                    >

                    <p class="text-lg mb-4">
                        Mastered by Disney animators, these 12 principles are the foundation of all compelling animation, making movement believable and engaging:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4 text-base grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-6">
                        <li>Squash and Stretch</li>
                        <li>Anticipation</li>
                        <li>Staging</li>
                        <li>Straight Ahead Action and Pose to Pose</li>
                        <li>Follow Through and Overlapping Action</li>
                        <li>Slow In and Slow Out</li>
                        <li>Arcs</li>
                        <li>Secondary Action</li>
                        <li>Timing</li>
                        <li>Exaggeration</li>
                        <li>Solid Drawing</li>
                        <li>Appeal</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-lg">
                        <strong class="text-cyan-300">Watch an in-depth explanation here:</strong>
                        <a href="https://youtu.be/uDqjIdI4bF4?si=EBgtSB8i_K8TzvJ-" target="_blank" class="text-cyan-400 hover:underline font-bold transition duration-150">
                            The 12 Principles of Animation (Explained)
                        </a>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- 3. Tips and Tricks -->
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white mb-4 border-b border-cyan-700 pb-2">Tips and Tricks for Efficiency</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3 ml-4 text-lg">
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Use Reference:</strong> Don't try to draw from memory! Use video, mirrors, or real-life footage to observe motion.</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Keep it Simple:</strong> Start with stick figures or simple shapes. Complexity comes later.</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Work in Layers:</strong> Separate elements (character, background, foreground) onto different layers to allow for easier edits.</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Save Constantly:</strong> Animation files can crash! Get into the habit of hitting Ctrl+S (or Cmd+S) every few minutes.</li>
                        <li><strong class="text-cyan-300">Test Your Work:</strong> Play your animation back at the intended speed often to catch mistakes early.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

